</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="59" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,644]" pageId="1" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,334,511,536]" pageId="1" pageNumber="59">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[347,488,512,536]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="Pulmomerus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[347,488,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="59">Pulmomerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a very distinctive genus, and is the only one described at the moment with extremely reduced hemelytra and without metathoracic wings. The spermatheca is also unique in the group. The lack of ocelli is another character that shows how modified the species is, and how its isolation in the Peninsula of Baja California probably has developed these singular characters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
